cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL, cs.CAT, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with semantics of programming languages, which is a topic closely related to logic. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category as game semantics is often used to study the complexity of programs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with interpreting types and programs in the context of programming languages. 
- cs.CAT (Category Theory) is a relevant category as the paper uses category theory to refine the abstract construction of game semantics. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with game semantics, which is a topic at the intersection of computer science and game theory.
